The paper proposes a new approach for Big Data mining and analysis, specifically for data clustering tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). The paper also focuses on spatial datasets, which could further narrow down the potential sub-categories to cs.DB and cs.DS.
